<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="bag-ice-cream" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Ice Cream (Bag)</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>One gallon-sized zip bag</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>One quart-sized zip bag</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup half &amp; hal</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>1 tablespoon sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>1 \frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoons vanilla</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>3 cups ice</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{3}</m> cup kosher/ice cream salt</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix half &amp; half, sugar, and vanilla together.  Pour into quart-sized bag, pressing out air.  Set aside.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Fill gallon-sized bag with ice (roughly half the bag); sprinkle with kosher/ice cream salt; and place the smaller bag in the larger bag.  Press out air and seal.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          With towel or oven mitts, hold the bag and shake for about 10-15 minutes.  Check ice cream mixture periodically to make sure it is firming up.  If not, add more ice and salt.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          When ice cream mixture is firm, eat up.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>